The paper focuses on using deep learning algorithms for neuroimaging data analysis and clinical data analysis to predict the conversion of mild cognitive impairments to Alzheimer's Disease. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing medical images, and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) as it involves training models to predict outcomes. Additionally, the paper mentions using natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) to analyze clinical data.
